id: pmc-w906
title: Add --item-url-base option to make pm item IDs clickable links
description: "When --item-url-base is supplied, each pm item ID in the changelog is rendered as a markdown hyperlink pointing to the item's .toon file. The type subdirectory (issues/, tasks/, chores/, features/, epics/) is resolved automatically from the item type field, so all item types are correctly linked without any per-type configuration."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: changelog,feature,github,links
created_at: "2026-05-24T12:25:27.480Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T12:25:41.498Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T00:00:00.000Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "- --item-url-base <url> CLI flag accepted. - Item IDs rendered as [pmc-abc](url/issues/pmc-abc.toon) (type dir derived from item type). - Works for all pm item types (Issue, Task, Chore, Feature, Epic). - 19 tests pass. - changelog:check passes after regeneration."
reviewer: steve
risk: low
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-production
release: v2026.05.24-7
resolution: "Implemented itemUrlBase in types.ts, generator.ts, cli.ts. Added itemTypeToDir() to derive type subdirectory from item.type. Test 5 added and passing. docs/usage.md updated."
expected_result: Item IDs in changelog are clickable links to correct type subdirectory .toon files on GitHub. 19 tests pass.
actual_result: "19/19 tests pass including new itemUrlBase test covering Issue, Chore, Task types. changelog:check passes after regeneration."
